description._content: Catalog #: 09_01653 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Long Beach California Additional Information: Squadron ""A"" in military uniform summer 1937, Long Beach California. Harry Haw not in this group, Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
